The paper deals with the complexity of decision, search, and optimization problems in logarithmic space, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also involves the study of Boolean formulas and their satisfiability, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of sub-linear space and the investigation of size parameters suggest a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and complexity theory (cs.LO). Finally, the paper proposes a new working hypothesis for the solvability of a specific problem, which could potentially have implications for artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
